    <h2>off the clock</h2>
    <p>
      I build things that don't need a roadmap review: an
      <a href="/work/rakhsh/">always-on agent that takes orders over
      iMessage</a>, a computer vision pipeline that
      <a href="/work/nba-video-analysis/">watches NBA games from
      broadcast video</a>, and a
      <a href="/work/poe-league-tools/">leveling copilot for Path of
      Exile</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The common thread: systems that are honest about what they know.
      Models that abstain instead of guessing, and agents whose authority
      is bounded by structure, not by politeness. As AI systems get real
      autonomy, I think that stops being taste and starts being safety.
    </p>

